posts.post_content: Posted By: Rhett Yeakley APRIL 2006 FOR SALE/TRADE list: Prices do not include shipping and insurance. 1.)1887 Baby Tobin Lithographs King Kelly (Baby Kelly). $180.00 2.)1888 WG1 John Coleman & Piano Legs Gore. Both appear Nrmt on front, but for samll stains on the backs, both currently in PSA 3 holders $495.00/Each 3.)1896 N301 Mayo Cut Plug Runner NY-Bent Forward -Nice shape $105.00 4.)1902 W601 Sporting Life Composites of New Haven (CT-League), Butte (NW League), and Rockford (IN-IL League) -All have 2 punch holes (as produced in 1902) and were at one time part of the bound version of these premiums. $105/Each. 5.)1904 Stenzels Rooters Pin Jack Sutthoff -Extremely rare pin featuring Cincinnati Reds players, Paper backing fully intact. Couple tiny spots of foxing on front. Uncatologued, recent discovery. $695.00 6.)1909 Obak Roy McArdle (Borderless back- Hand Cut) Clean back, with slight irregular cut. $90.00 7.)(25) 1910 Sweet Caporal Domino Discs -25 different discs including Mardecai Brown, Home Run Baker, Eddie Grant, and extremely tough Home/Visiting Team Disc. Condition is overall very nice most around EX, only 3 lesser condition. Nice jump start on a set. $575.00/Lot 8.)1911 T3 Turkey Red #105 Hans Lobert -Clean card w/ no pinholes, back is clean but for a former collectors neat signature at the top. $195.00 9.)1914 E145 Cracker Jack #72 Joe Boehling -SGC 3 $125.00 10.)1915 E145 Cracker Jacks #54 Marty O’Toole, #155 Joe Connolly -Both SGC 4 (VGEX) $110.00/Each 11.)1915 PM1 Ornate Frame Pins Dick Hoblitzel -Photo portion light and slightly scuffed, frame very nice. $195.00 12.)1923 W572 Strip of 10 (Grover Alexander, Zach Wheat, Veach, O’Farrell, etc.) -No creases, extremely clean $285.00 13.)(Two) 1926-29 Exhibit Tris Speaker PC’s -Awesome colors (Bright pink/purple & Orange). Both are the tougher “no background” versions. No creases clean backs ((SOLD)) 14.)1926-29 PC Exhibits Hack Wilson (Black/White) nice creaseless card with couple tiny stains on back. $105.00 15.)1927 FC59 Honey Boy Ice Cream #3 Carson McVey (Transcona) -Lower grade but clean back $225.00 16.)1930 W517 Paul Waner NO NUMBER ON FRONT (Only recently catalogued) Nice full borders $150.00 17.)1933 R308 Tattoo Orbit Jimmy Dykes. Not bad image for the issue, small amount of paper damage on reverse. $50.00 18.)1934 Goudey Albums National League. Cover shows some wear but is intact, inside pages have damage. Extremely tough item, displays well. $75.00 19.)(8) 1936 Diamond Match Co. (Cubs) Demaree, French, Frey, Galan, O’Dea, Parmalee, Root, Stainbeck. All pretty nice with intact strickers, but all have a small # written on the reverse in pen. $40.00 /Lot 20.)1943 La Ambrosia Regla Team set. (12 cards) Low grade with most cards exhibiting back damage.) Still a tough issue, good bang for the buck. $35.00/Lot 21.)1946-49 Sports Exchange Series 7 (Joe DiMaggio, Ralph Kiner, Henrich, Travis, Vic Lombardi, Lavagetto, Sam Chapman, Casey, Bevens) + Jimmy Foxx. Also comes with the original Mailing envelope for the 7th series. Extremely tough. $175.00/Lot 22.)(3) 1930's Diamond Hockey Matchbooks (Silver) -Very clean w/complete strikers -Murry Murdoch, Johnny Sheppard, Chris Speyers. $60.00 [IMG]http://www.network54.com/Realm/tmp/1144008871.JPG[/IMG] [IMG]http://www.network54.com/Realm/tmp/1144008922.JPG[/IMG] [IMG]http://www.network54.com/Realm/tmp/1143951712.JPG[/IMG] [IMG]http://www.network54.com/Realm/tmp/1143951793.JPG[/IMG] [IMG]http://www.network54.com/Realm/tmp/1143951960.JPG[/IMG] Email me with any questions at rhettyeakley@netzero.com, Again all items are for sale for the prices indicated, but would also consider trading for items I am interested in... many of the above items can be seen at my website: [URL="http://www.geocities.com/rhettmatthew_37/prewar.html"][URL="http://www.geocities.com/rhettmatthew_37/prewar.html>"]http://www.geocities.com/rhettmatthew_37/prewar.html
